<title><![CDATA[I wrote this in the wake of Roe v Wade being overturned and sadl...]]></title>
<link>https://imginn.com/p/DCMw51Cyxvc/</link>
<guid>https://imginn.com/p/DCMw51Cyxvc/</guid>
<description>
<![CDATA[<a href="https://instagram.com/p/DCMw51Cyxvc/">View on Instagram</a><p><img src="https://scontent-bos5-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.29350-15/466469731_1742720333148421_1729951873272171479_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e15_fr_p1080x1080_tt6&_nc_ht=scontent-bos5-1.cdninstagram.com&_nc_cat=101&_nc_ohc=u7Wg6PPB9r4Q7kNvgEPzT5u&_nc_gid=fbc6f9c83ee241f1984c94113117e03a&edm=AGenrX8BAAAA&ccb=7-5&oh=00_AYALL6ktNrd1MVr7TNjwLXGnWe6iX454WOgwBI1Llkj9rw&oe=6750A061&_nc_sid=ed990e" /><br>I wrote this in the wake of Roe v Wade being overturned and sadly it remains as relevant now as it was then. How are you guys? Personally, I’m still recovering from election-induced vertigo. Listening to and reading the words of others who know more than I do about the historical and economic conditions that brought us to this moment is helping. So are walks and diminished 7th chords.I do know that I ended this “My Country Tis of Thee” rewrite two years ago on a wildly hopeful stanza and I still think that was the right call. The fight for a better America wasn’t over then and it certainly isn’t now. We’ll get back to the marching when we find our footing. For now, take care of yourself. You are not alone.]]>
</description>
<pubDate>Sun, 10 Nov 2024 03:27:17 -0500</pubDate>
</item>
